[[File:Agap logo.jpg|right|200px]]
The '''Agricultural Sector Alliance of the Philippines, Inc.''' ('''AGAP''') is a [[political party|party-list]] in the [[Philippines]]. In the 14 May 2007 [[Philippine general election, 2007|election]], the party originally won 3 seats in the nationwide party-list vote but 2 of them were disqualified. In the [[Philippine general election, 2010|2010]], AGAP one 1 seat, down from 2, while in the [[Philippine general election, 2013|next election]], they regained a seat with 592,463 (2.14% of the popular vote), the most successful election AGAP has had so far.

