'''Megan Dunn''' (born 1990/91) is a British student politician, and the former president of the UK's [[National Union of Students (United Kingdom)|National Union of Students]].<ref name="theguardian1"/><ref>{{cite web|last=Gurney |first=Josie |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/education/universityeducation/student-life/11555304/Megan-Dunn-elected-as-NUS-president-we-will-make-sure-students-arent-lied-to-again.html |title=Megan Dunn elected as NUS president: 'we will make sure students aren't lied to again' |publisher=Telegraph |date=2015-04-22 |accessdate=2016-05-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Havergal |first=Chris |url=https://www.timeshighereducation.com/news/megan-dunn-faces-nus-leadership-challenge |title=Megan Dunn faces NUS leadership challenge &#124; Times Higher Education (THE) |publisher=Times Higher Education |date=2016-05-05 |accessdate=2016-05-15}}</ref>
Dunn campaigned for the United Kingdom to remain in the [[European Union]] in the [[United Kingdom European Union membership referendum, 2016|2016 referendum]], having been appointed to the board of the [[Britain Stronger in Europe]] campaign.<ref>{{cite web|last=Leftly |first=Mark |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/eu-referendum-caroline-lucas-and-nus-president-unveiled-as-members-of-in-campaign-board-a6689261.html |title=EU referendum: Caroline Lucas and NUS president unveiled as members of In Campaign board &#124; The Independent |publisher=The Independent |date=2015-10-10 |accessdate=2016-08-16}}</ref>
