{{About|Nisekoi film|manga series|Nisekoi}} {{Infobox film | name = Nisekoi: False Love | image = | alt = | caption = | film name = {{film name|kanji=ニセコイ|romaji=Nisekoi}} | director = Hayato Kawai | producer = Tamako Tsujimoto | writer = {{ubl|Shota Koyama|Noriaki Sugihara}} | based on = {{based on|''[[Nisekoi]]''|[[Naoshi Komi]]}} | starring = {{ubl|[[Kento Nakajima]]|[[Ayami Nakajo]]|Natsumi Ikema|[[Haruka Shimazaki]]|Kaede Aono|Yūta Kishi}} | music = Yu Takami | cinematography = Shinya Kimura | editing = Honosuke Hagaki | studio = {{ubl|FINE Entertainment|[[Toho|Toho Pictures]]}} | distributor = {{ubl|Toho}} | released = {{film date|2018|12|21}} | runtime = 118 minutes | country = [[Japan]] | language = Japanese | budget = | gross = }} {{Nihongo|'''''Nisekoi: False Love'''''|ニセコイ|Nisekoi|lead=yes}} is an upcoming 2018 Japanese film adaptation of a [[manga]] series [[Nisekoi|of the same name]] by [[Naoshi Komi]]. It is directed by Hayato Kawai, distributed by [[Toho]], and stars [[Kento Nakajima]] and [[Ayami Nakajo]] as Raku Ichijo and Chitoge Kirisaki respectively. It will be released in Japan on December 21, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://eiga.com/news/20180423/3|title=「ニセコイ」実写化、主演は中島健人×中条あやみ！偽の恋めぐり大ゲンカぼっ発!?|accessdate=April 24, 2018|work=eiga.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://eiga.com/movie/89091|title=ニセコイ|work=eiga.com|language=Japanese}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-04-15/nisekoi-romantic-comedy-manga-gets-live-action-film-in-december/.130316|title=Nisekoi Romantic Comedy Manga Gets Live-Action Film in December|website=Anime News Network|date=April 15, 2018|accessdate=April 15, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url= https://mantan-web.jp/article/20180422dog00m200029000c.html|title= 中島健人＆中条あやみ：実写映画「ニセコイ」で初共演でダブル主演 脱王子、脱清純宣言！|newspaper= まんたんウェブ |publisher= 株式会社MANTAN |date= 2018-04-23|accessdate=2018-04-23}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cinematoday.jp/news/N0100171|title=「ニセコイ」実写映画化！ジャンプ人気のラブコメ、今冬に公開決定|accessdate=April 17, 2018|work=Cinema today}}</ref> The theme song of the film, KawaE by Yabai T-Shirts Yasan.
==Cast== * [[Kento Nakajima]] as Raku Ichijo * [[Ayami Nakajo]] as Chitoge Kirisaki * Natsumi Ikema as Kosaki Onodera * [[Haruka Shimazaki]] as Marika Tachibana * Kaede Aono as Seshirō Tsugumi * Yūta Kishi as Shū Maiko: Raku’s best friend. * Hana Kawamura as Ruri Miyamoto: Kosaki’s best friend. * [[Daigo (musician)|DAIGO]] as Claude: Chitoge’s bodyguard. * [[Marika Matsumoto]] as Kyoko Hihara: The homeroom teacher of Raku’s classroom.
